##He brought nearly 80,000 doses into Hubei

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
PCR Laboratory of Hubei Provincial People's Hospital.

This article is about 4483 words long

Estimated reading time: 12 minutes

By Qin Zhenzi

Editor Cong Yuhua

Qiu Chen's holiday turned into a journey.

In the last month, he has brought nearly 80,000 kits into a once-closed market in Hubei Province, where traffic is blocked.

Around the Spring Festival, there was a shortage of nucleic acid test kits in Hubei province to diagnose new coronary pneumonia. In Wuhan, some patients queued overnight for the test. Outside Wuhan, a large number of grass-roots hospitals do not have such rare materials, testing equipment and environmental conditions.

Qiu Chen is a salesman. He sees a business opportunity in the gap. The scope of the "closed city" continued to expand, he "bought" the location of the constantly changing, those days, he pulled the reagent box of the minivan is a "red line" edge of a tenacious coordinates.

"I wanted to do business from the beginning, " Qiu Chen said. It would be many days before he realized that things were changing as he went along.

1

The first shipment arrived at 2:00 a.m. , serving 1,000 people, in three foam crates filled with ice.

In the past, small volume, light weight nucleic acid detection products are shun Feng cold chain. At this time, the field into Wuhan Logistics has been stopped. It's the eighth day of the Spring Festival travel rush, and train and plane tickets are hard to get. The company assigned an employee who was going home through Wuhan to get on the train with the kit.

The train stopped at Hankou Railway Station, and Qiu Chen was on the platform, carrying a box in the darkness.

He and his colleagues then took the kits to cold storage at the distributor, where they were pointed at 4:30 a.m. . A few hours later, the kits for seven hundred people were sent to fifty hospitals in Hubei Province via a functioning provincial logistics network.

This is January 19,2020, the network is circulating "Wuhan Fengcheng" hearsay, Qiu Chen said there was a sense of foreboding, "to come true. ".

On January 21, he received feedback from more than 20 hospitals that the test results of the kit were satisfactory and needed to be ordered.

"I want to do this market up! " Qiu Chen and company communication, emergency start production line.

At 2 am on January 22nd, in Hankou Railway Station, 5,000 people's kits arrived. The kits were quickly sent to more than a dozen hospitals in Huanggang, Xiaogan, Shiyan and Suizhou.

On the same day, several financial media reported that only three enterprises were designated by the National Health Commission to produce the new diagnostic reagent for pneumonia, they are: Shanghai Huirui Biotechnology Co. , Ltd. , Shanghai Geno Biotechnology Co. , Ltd. , Shanghai Berger Medical Technology Co. , Ltd. , for the National Disease Control, Hubei Province and the provinces and cities CDC testing.

In fact, the Chinese scientific community announced the deciphered genome of the new coronavirus around the world as early as January 10, and many domestic pharmaceutical companies, including Qiu Chen's company, have started to develop detection products.

A few days later, dozens of domestic enterprises have developed similar products, without the State Drug Administration approval, did not get the "registration certificate. ". "designated" means that some enterprises' products are allowed to "first emergency" , the National Health Commission unified deployment of these testing reagents for designated hospitals at all levels, CDC use. There is no pricing and no need for a "registration certificate" .

As early as five or six days ago, Qiu Chen had heard that his "employer" was not on the "designated list" . He began to be a little surprised, "the designated three in the field of nucleic acid testing does not seem well-known, " but he thought, the state-designated enterprises, stocks must be sufficient, quality is not a problem, the hospital out of concern for risk, companies that are not on the list are generally not used.

"Let's go to bed. We're done. " On January 17, he returned to his hometown in Suizhou, Hubei Province, "Xiao Nian, have a holiday! " Did Not expect to receive the next day department manager notice: "Back to Wuhan, things have turned around. " Many hospitals reagent box demand suddenly increased, "to goods. ".

"It was not a panic, but a business opportunity, " Qiu Chen said.

2

The third batch of kits containing 10,000 doses was sent from the head office on the afternoon of January 22.

On this day, the train stopped at Wuhan Station.

Qiu chose Macheng North Railway Station, which is located in the Huanggang district, two hours' drive from downtown Wuhan and "considered as a transit station" .

At 9:30 pm, Qiu Chen received the goods at the North Railway Station of Macheng and sent the refrigerated truck directly to the People's Hospital of Macheng to deliver the urgently needed 500-person test kits.

On Feb. 11, Qiu Chen was asked by his company to donate kits to the Huanggang and Huangshi Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

At the time, the full extent of the Huanggang outbreak was not yet apparent, and the hospital did not appear to be crowded. Qiu Chen to a director of the Inspection Department call: "afraid these are not enough, want to prepare a little? Give you 1000 people, do not pay first, can use. "

The director sounded hesitant, he recalled, "although the quality of the product is recognized, but I guess it is considered that there is no 'registration certificate' and no verification, " and finally reluctantly agreed, "stay here and send it to other hospitals as needed. "

The next morning, the director of the telephone on the call: "Small Qiu, goods we also want. "

On January 23rd, the city of Wuhan was closed.

That morning, the Daye People's Hospital in Huangshi, Hubei Province, called. "There was an urgent need for a kit. ". At this time, the dealer's three trucks in Wuhan, Xiangyang, Jingzhou delivery. Qiu Chen used his private car. The driver, an old master familiar with highways and country lanes in Hubei Province, had spent four or five hours in Wuhan, unable to leave the city.

All highway exits were closed, some provincial roads were cut off by the public, and some minor roads were blocked by obstacles. Finally, the master changed cars, contact the high-speed checkpoint to explain the situation, at five or six in the afternoon finally rushed out of Wuhan. More than 20 hospitals in Jingmen, Daye, Guangshui and Jingzhou received the kits.

On January 24, according to media reports, the relevant head of the Marketing Department of China bio-shanghai Geno Biotechnology Co. , a subsidiary of China Pharmaceutical Group Co. , Ltd. , said, the company has already supplied more than 1000 boxes (50,000 people) of COVID-19 test kits in Wuhan, and the production capacity has been further expanded on the 23rd for use in all regions of the country with Wuhan as the focus. According to each kit can be used for 50 people to calculate, the current kit production capacity has been used for hundreds of thousands of people test.

Wu Yue, a purchasing officer in Wuhan of Sinopharm Group, told the China Youth Daily website that the group will release purchasing information to him. He needs to connect customers with product resources, contact the manufacturer to arrange delivery and complete the "upstream and downstream docking. ". In the early stage, the purchased materials will be sent directly to the hospital, and in the later stage, these materials will start to be uniformly distributed by the CDC at all levels.

Wu Yue said he was very impressed, New Year's Eve, the first day and the second day of the Lunar New Year, are all "phone constantly. ". At 8:00 am on the first day of the New Year, the group called and said it wanted to purchase 20,000 units of NUCLEIC ACID test kits.

News of the lack of supplies in Hubei's front-line health facilities hit the headlines every day, and social networking sites can see a large number of patients who are unable to get a diagnosis without a test kit. "Masks, protective clothing, reagent boxes were all missing, " Wu recalled. "Not only was I shopping, but others were shopping, too, but many times the customers were out of stock. "

3

On January 25, just after 5 p.m. on the first day of the Lunar New Year, Qiu Chen received a notice that the Hubei Provincial People's hospital needed 5,000 people's kits. He immediately went to pick up the goods and was taken to the hospital after 6 o'clock. "The quality is the foundation, we still quite have the confidence, otherwise also dare not sell" .

The lab was on the first floor, he recalled, and he was wearing a mask and a shoe holster as he carried boxes from the parking lot to the clinic building. I didn't see anyone, but I was really nervous. The Central Youth Daily Central Youth Net reporter looked at Hubei Province People's Hospital examination department doctor to Qiu Chen's "receipt" , is uses the white paper handwriting "the White Note" . In those days, it was a common situation. Qiu Chen said frankly, "Baitiao on Baitiao, the money can not be collected, when the donation. ".

He worried about the company's production capacity, afraid of late Provincial People's hospital 10,000 units of reagent box can not be supplied. One piece of good news is that on this day, the National Health Commission cancelled the recommendation of nucleic acid testing products and test kits. This is equivalent to opening up the list of "reagent box procurement" , along with more than a dozen enterprises including Qiu Chen Company, the Kit can be sent to a hospital with relative compliance. The State Drug Administration has opened a fast track for approval. Four companies were approved on January 26th, and the list has grown ever since.

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, Qiu Chen found that the company's production line fully started, all over the country's market departments are to headquarters for goods. The Test Kit for 20,000 people originally scheduled to arrive in Wuhan on the 3rd day has been postponed to the 4th day. Qiu Chen studied the mobile phone map for half a day, and discussed with colleagues in the Wechat Group, and finally selected the delivery place.

On the night of January 28, a delivery truck and a pick-up truck were parked at opposite ends of the provincial border at a high-speed toll booth in Hubei Province. "I'm not going out until you come in. ". Boxes full of reagent boxes were manually unloaded and passed through a pedestrian passageway under the toll station into Hubei. Two days later, the kits were all distributed.

In the photos taken by the staff at that time, some people counting boxes, some people carrying the boxes climbed the long steps, cross-province "delivery. ".

As of February 10,2020, Qiu's company had issued nearly 700,000 new coronavirus nucleic acid test kits, "but by January 25, " he said, "What we were doing at the hospital terminal was technically against the rules, " he said, recalling that the company had told employees not to stick to the rules, not to be afraid in times of emergency.

According to Qiu Chen, in fact, in order to be diagnosed, it is not enough to have a kit, but also to have a PCR fluorescence analyzer, and to have laboratory conditions that meet the "15189" standard, so that testing can be done, "The early opening of 10 institutions, some hospitals are not on the list, secretly step on the red line to do. ". Later, Hubei Province, a number of hospitals emergency procurement of equipment installed, a number of private qualified institutions have also been allowed to participate in testing.

The engineer who installed the PCR equipment in the back Lake area of Wuhan Central Hospital.

According to the second edition of the guidelines for laboratory detection of COVID-19 pneumonia issued by the National Health Commission, there are two targets for nucleic acid detection (real-time fluorescent RT-PCR) , and the diagnosis can only be confirmed if both targets are positive.

New problems have emerged, some experts questioned, the influx of test kits to the market, the quality is uneven, some patients have to go through multiple tests to determine the results.

4

It was supposed to be a influenza fall / Winter season.

Qiu Chen Remembers, a hospital in Wuhan detects a stream and B stream when the use of "reagent box" , a number of up. "The sales volume is so big, this year's task is accomplished by this, can get bonus! "

On the evening of December 30,2019, several screenshots of wechat chats and a set of videos began circulating on the Internet, roughly describing an unexplained pneumonia infection in Wuhan. Of the 27 cases identified, seven are in critical condition, the rest are under control, and two are expected to be discharged soon, a viral pneumonia official said on Dec. 31. Most of the cases were in south China Seafood City, Kong Hon District, Wuhan.

"It sounds under control, " said Qiu Chen, who left Wuhan after New Year's Day 2020 for his annual meeting in the provincial headquarters. "It's not that serious. There's no business opportunity. ". Central China's population density, humidity is also large, influenza detection products sales "among the best, " Qiu Chen completed the sales task, colleagues discussed, for the products in the future respiratory "very market. ".

"there were a lot of people on the street" when he returned to Wuhan from his annual meeting on January 8,2020.

On January 15, Qiu Chen received a phone call. A former colleague reminded him that several doctors at Wuhan Union Hospital had contracted pneumonia of unknown origin, one of whom was critically ill and had been put on a respirator, and that doctors at Golden Pool had contracted the infection earlier.

"In the industry, it's a sign. Doctors get infected, it's serious. " On the morning of January 16, qiu Chen to the Wuhan Union Hospital to "verify" , found that the infection department medical staff wearing protective clothing, wearing a mask, "in Wuhan more than 10 years, have not seen this formation.

On the way back to the subway, Qiu Chen observed that none of the passengers around wore masks. "Just arrested a few, I dare not say anything. " He thought of two things, one is to find a way to buy some masks for themselves, and the company's products may have a market.

"Do business originally, doing to become commonweal. " Qiu Chen is puzzled.

Under some invisible great power, many people are "involuntarily" .

A procurement kit distributors at first afraid of medical institutions can not pay, afraid of the government "accounting after the fall" , fall on the charge of "illegal business" , but still advance money to continue to buy.

A post-90s nurse had already taken a leave of absence, after sealing off the city, he took a patrol car of traffic police to the hospital to "support" . Qiu Chen met by chance and gave her a ride.

A female doctor has not seen her family since she began testing for the new coronavirus nucleic acid in the PCR laboratory at Central War zone General Hospital. Even though her husband works at the same hospital.

Qiu Chen also said frankly: "If I had known it would be sealed off, if I had known it would be so serious, I probably wouldn't have come back, I don't know. "

In early February, Wuhan's "reagent box" has no longer shortage, Qiu Chen busy to help the company arrange "donations" of materials and logistics. "No matter how much material comes in, all do not calculate sale achievement! " But this Hubei person can not stop.

On the morning of January 29, he went to Hubei Provincial People's Hospital, Auxiliary Hospital to do the company's new coronavirus nucleic acid test kit "clinical case report. ".

The original eye center was converted into an isolation ward. Qiu Chen accidentally learned that a doctor sent her mother-in-law to see a doctor, the result of the whole family "isolation on the spot. ". Someone said, "I didn't have time to buy anything. "

He immediately went downstairs and rushed to the supermarket across from the hospital to buy a washbasin, clothes hangers, sterile wipes and other items to send to the "completely unknown" doctor.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Qiu Chen purchased daily necessities for the family of the quarantined doctor.

He was leaving the parking lot when a car sideswiped his car. The driver looks flustered, compensate Qiu Chen 100 yuan.

"What are you flustered about? " Qiu Chen can not help asking.

"My mother died of that pneumonia, " was the reply.

Qiu Chen Leng for a while, he returned the money back.

(Qiu Chen and Wu Yue were given pseudonyms at the request of the interviewees. Images for this article are provided.)
